 **Natural Language Processing (NLP) Syllabus**

### **1. Introduction to NLP**

* Definition and importance of NLP
* Applications of NLP in real-world scenarios
* Challenges in NLP (ambiguity, context, sarcasm, etc.)
* NLP pipeline overview

### **2. Text Preprocessing**

* Tokenization (word, sentence, subword)
* Stopword removal
* Stemming and Lemmatization
* Lowercasing and text normalization
* Handling punctuation and special characters
* Handling emojis and slang

### **3. Linguistic Foundations**

* Morphology (structure of words)
* Syntax (grammar, parsing, POS tagging)
* Semantics (meaning of words and sentences)
* Pragmatics (context-based meaning)

### **4. Feature Representation of Text**

* Bag of Words (BoW)
* Term Frequency â€“ Inverse Document Frequency (TF-IDF)
* One-Hot Encoding
* Word Embeddings: Word2Vec, GloVe, FastText
* Contextual embeddings: ELMo, BERT, GPT

### **5. Language Modeling**

* n-gram Language Models
* Probability and perplexity in language models
* Neural Language Models
* Transformer-based models (BERT, GPT, T5, etc.)

### **6. Text Classification**

* Sentiment analysis
* Spam detection
* Topic classification
* Document categorization

### **7. Sequence Labeling Tasks**

* Part-of-Speech (POS) tagging
* Named Entity Recognition (NER)
* Chunking and Shallow parsing

### **8. Machine Translation**

* Rule-based translation
* Statistical Machine Translation (SMT)
* Neural Machine Translation (seq2seq models, attention mechanism, Transformer models)

### **9. Text Summarization**

* Extractive summarization techniques
* Abstractive summarization techniques
* Evaluation metrics (ROUGE, BLEU, METEOR)

### **10. Information Retrieval & Extraction**

* Search engines and ranking algorithms
* Question answering systems
* Information extraction (relations, events)

### **11. Dialogue Systems & Chatbots**

* Rule-based chatbots
* Retrieval-based chatbots
* Generative chatbots
* Conversational AI with transformers

### **12. Advanced NLP**

* Transfer Learning in NLP
* Pre-trained large language models (BERT, GPT, LLaMA, etc.)
* Prompt engineering and fine-tuning
* Few-shot and zero-shot learning in NLP
* Multilingual and cross-lingual NLP
* Low-resource NLP techniques

### **13. NLP for Speech & Multimodal Data**

* Speech recognition (ASR) basics
* Text-to-Speech (TTS)
* Speech-to-Text systems
* Multimodal NLP (vision + language models, e.g., CLIP, BLIP, Flamingo)

### **14. Evaluation Metrics in NLP**

* Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score
* Perplexity
* BLEU, ROUGE, METEOR, BERTScore

### **15. Ethical and Social Considerations in NLP**

* Bias in NLP models
* Fairness and inclusivity
* Privacy and data protection in NLP applications

